Rent to own available, responsible for all repairs if it happens!

Also, you can text to me: five zero seven, nine nine zero, five one six seven. Thanks. I do not answer any phone call, but you can left voice message though.

description:
Recently sold: $97,500. Be charmed by a fine single family home in a quiet neighborhood in Saint Paul. Since Morton Street East is a dead end road to the east, there is not much traffic that drives by and the few cars that do drive by are driving slowly due to the dead end road. You're an easy walk away from many restaurants, bars, coffee houses, parks, and shops all located on Cesar Chavez and State Street. And you're conveniently located within an easy 5 block walk to the #68 bus line (a handy line which runs between downtown St. Paul / Metro State University and Inver Hills Community College on Robert Street). Just think, you could live only a 5 minute drive away from downtown St.Paul! The living room and dining room feature hardwood floors. The spacious kitchen features a dishwasher. The unit has a brand new water heater! Please note that there is an additional UN-finished 400 square feet of private storage in the basement within this rental unit as well. In the basement there is a laundry machine and dryer and neither of those two appliances are coin operated. No more running to the convenience store for trade in your dollar bills for quarters for your laundry This rental unit is listed as a 3 bedroom unit but the middle bedroom upstairs is actually considered a loft because you need to walk through that "loft" in order to get to either bedroom. All 3 sleeping areas are upstairs adjacent to one another. Exciting new news! I am allowing pets. Pet rent per month per dog(s) is $50.00 and pet rent per month per cat(s) is $50.00. FYI - Typically I charge $200.00 per pet for a non-refundable pet deposit. Renters are responsible to pay for all of the utilities. I apologize but this property is NOT Section 8 approved. I want to bring to your attention that the backyard is fenced in which is perfect for dogs and little kids. Beyond the fenced in backyard to the north is another terraced section of land I own that could be used for gardening if you wanted to put in the hard work to restore that unused area for your own personal garden(s)! The Area of land beyond the back yard to the north is probably about 40 feet wide by about 60 feet deep - and most of that land is terraced, FYI. This 1120 square foot single family home is VERY clean and deserves showing. You will be pleased with what you see. Off street parking is available for this property. This home does NOT have a garage, sorry. Move into this home as early as Monday, June 10, 2019! The fastest way to get ahold of me is to text/call me and/or reply to this ad and I will email you back shortly answering any question(s) you may have and/or set up a viewing appointment of the rental property. As of 10:00 A.M. on Friday, June 7th I have a showing opening at 1:45 P.M. on Friday, June 7th. (This rental property is near St.Paul & West St.Paul & South St. Paul & Inver Grove Heights & West Side .) We'd prefer you to sign a lease thru the end of June 2020. (We are sometimes flexible though.) Move in as soon as Monday, June 10, 2019! We are looking for someone to sign the lease who has a combined minimum gross monthly income of $3,400.00 and who also does not have an unlawful detainer(s) nor a felony on their record. We are also looking for a minimum credit score of 620. Tenants are responsible for all utilities.

Must have a minimum credit score of 620. I am looking for someone with no evictions and no felonies. Gross monthly household income must be no less than $3400.00 a month.
